description:
This fillacello pendant from Bo Howe's most recent batch of work features one of the most unique designs and color schemes he has made. Bo meticulously creates some of the most intricate and beautiful fillacello designs -- this piece being a shining example of his best work. This is one of the larger pieces Bo has made. This piece measures 2.5 inches tall by 2 inches wide

There are only four other black and white pieces by Bo and they all have a unique design.  This piece is ti signed "Bobo 2013 4/5 b/w."

name: Rob Davis Mini-Rig Honeycomb Set
description:
The most recent series of Mini-Rigs being made by local artist, Rob Davis. This awesome honeycomb and line-work set comes with the rig, dome and matching dish. The joints are hand-ground, fully worked 14mm and look ridiculously classy. Everywhere you look on these pieces there is super badass line-work coming out at every angle. Rob placed his incredible honeycomb technique over the two main discs on the rig, creating a worked transparent viewing window. The mini rig stands six inches tall and has a natural perc. The mini rig is signed on the bottom "Davis 2013."

Stands 6 inches tall.

Must be 18 years or older to purchase.

Original price of $550

name: Harold Williams Cooney Carved "Drop" Pendant (A)
description:
From Harold's Nevada Trade Bead Collection this is a hollow blown carved drop pendant with hollow bail.

Nevada Trade Beads are one of ﬁfty-ﬁve state and territory named design groups being developed for the American Trade Bead Permanent Collection, an encyclopedic like study of glass beadmaking technique slated for completion in July of 2035.

Nevada Trade Beads study the cold revealing of coil potted cane. After the ﬂameworking was completed, the item's surface was sandblasted and oiled to give it a pleasingly tactile, natural satin ﬁnish.

name: Double Sided "SER" Key Pendant with 24'' Byzantine Chain
description:
Part of a series of key pendants by Christopher "SER" Lee this piece features the symbol of the ouroboros (a snake/dragon eating itself), symbolizing self-reflexivity or cyclicality. It is double sided and made out of Arg. Silver, two stones adorn the eyes on either side. This piece hangs from a 24 inch. 14/20 Gold-Fill and Argentina Silver Byzantine Chain made by Mike Zeiters, which contains 633 individual rings and has a large lobster style clasp. 

Chain is available separately for $450.
Pendant is available separately for $250. 

Use the contact form at the top of the page or send an email to drew@headyhunter.com with inquiries.

name: David Sigler Dichroic Vortex Marble (A)
description:

It feels weird to have your finger on the back of the marble because the vortex looks like it spirals downwards about 3-4 inches and the marble is only 2 inches in diameter. The surface work on the back and lensing of the vortex are also really clean, pretty and uniform throughout. This marble is ti signed "DS 9/13" on the back.

Measures 2.00 inches in diameter.

name: Rob Davis Air Trapped Retticello & Honeycomb Set
description:
A mash up by three local, Eugene artisans, Rob Davis on the glass, Paul Powers on the wood and Ryan Lofte on the metal. The rig, sherlock & dish by Rob, who until recently apprenticed under Marcel Braun, features super tightly woven retticellos with air traps between the stringers and awesome honeycomb work. These pieces are elegant in hand and sit beautifully on the custom stand, made out of Maple Burl, by Paul & Ryan, which can be taken apart for easy travel and assembly. The rig has 14mm handground, fully worked joints and a natural perc. 

Sherlock stands 9 inches tall from bottom of the base to the top of the mouth piece while resting on the stand. The mini rig stands 5 inches tall. 

Must be 18 years or older to purchase.

Original price - $750
